  "prompt": "How many keywords are there in the COBOL programming language in the latest version?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, COBOL (Common Business-Oriented Language) has a standardized set of keywords defined by the COBOL 2002 standard and subsequent updates, including the COBOL 2014 and COBOL 2020 standards. The exact number of keywords can vary slightly depending on the specific dialect and implementation of COBOL, but generally, there are around 200 keywords in COBOL. \n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding the number of keywords in the latest COBOL version, you may want to consult the official COBOL specification documents or a reliable resource pertaining to the specific implementation you are interested in.",
